default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOf all the unlikely 
defaultIPCC
default statements on human-induced global warming, its announcement of "95 per cent certainty" that this is the case fits in with previous dodgy statistics. Whether it identifies 97 per cent or 83 per cent "certainty", it simply means that it is not certain.
